+{"id":"frankentorch-s56","title":"Implement general N-D tensor_kron instead of 1D/2D placeholder","description":"mock-code-finder found a real placeholder in crates/ft-api/src/lib.rs: tensor_kron only handles (1D,1D) and (2D,2D), then returns ShapeMismatch for all other rank combinations with the comment 'For simplicity, only support 1D and 2D for now'. PyTorch torch.kron supports arbitrary-rank tensors after left-padding the lower-rank operand with singleton dimensions, with output shape dim_i = a_dim_i * b_dim_i. Fix tensor_kron to compute general rank-aligned row-major Kronecker products, preserve the existing 1D/2D behavior, fail closed on shape-volume overflow, and add tests covering mixed-rank and 3D cases.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T19:40:07.093666383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T19:46:05.952847864Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T19:46:05.951085596Z","close_reason":"Implemented general rank-aligned tensor_kron with mixed-rank and 3D regression tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
