+{"id":"frankentorch-sre","title":"Native state dict serialization rejects F16/BF16 tensors","description":"testing-conformance-harnesses found a serialization contract gap in crates/ft-serialize/src/lib.rs. Native FrankenTorch state dict save/load only maps DType::F64 and DType::F32 to dtype tags, while ft-core DenseTensor and SafeTensors serialization already support DType::F16 and DType::BF16. This means half-precision tensors cannot round-trip through save_state_dict/load_state_dict even though the tensor stack supports them. Add stable native dtype tags for F16/BF16, encode/decode their 2-byte little-endian payloads, update the old unsupported-dtype test, and add round-trip coverage for F16 and BF16.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T19:41:25.813383663Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T19:41:28.648125643Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
